our history of AoW attempts went like this, No one up until us had even attempted AoW except for the top 3, therefore I asked I can't remember if it was Ootampa or Emil or something, if we could attempt AoW on their turn. They said fine, we lost to AoW getting it to a small percent, while fighting an unslowed Idol of Rallos Zek.<br>
<br>
Afterwhich about 4 other guilds decided since LoM can do AoW they should take a shot at it too, this resulted in the guilds currently on the rotation losing their AoW's to burnage. <br>
<br>
Therefore the new statue rule was put into play, LoM then fought AoW a second time on our statue and won. After which a newer rule to my knowledge was implimented that you could try AoW every AoW full cycle, after VoF won I think the rule was changed back. Forgive me if I left something out, I'v been out of the country for 2 weeks. <br>
<br>
Basically this is why the rule is the way it is.<br>
<br>
Anyone and their grandma can beat a slowed Idol, its not much harder then Statue so therefore, just about anyone can have a shot at AoW, whether they have a force close to killing him or not.  <p>Xedd Zerous<br>
